URL reference: https://itnext.io/local-platform-engineering-on-your-laptop-vind-sveltos-and-argocd-2b3e1341ebe7
DateReviewed: 2026-06-04
Description: Today's piece is a blog of sorts, about someone sitting down to build some stuff, breaking some stuff and discovering a useful tool in the meantime. Our author is experienced at Kubernetes, and seemingly a developer at one time. We start the piece with background, and then dive in - managing Kubernetes when you have a few clusters can be challenging. You have different configs, teams, providers. You end up with a mishmash of scripts. To the rescue, it seems is Sveltos. You have to deploy it to all of your clusters, and there are a few pre-reqs, but Sveltos handles orchestrating K8s. Add the right label and Sveltos makes the cluster get to the state; remove it and Sveltos cleans it up. He does mention some security things to think about, but also goes through a bunch of the little pieces that make it nice to run clusters more easily. It supports Helm charts, YAML, and a few other config tools. It integrates with Flux and ArgoCD. And he goes through a pretty thorough install and walk through, with a second part promised soon.
BottomLine: Walk through of a tool to manage multiple Kubernetes clusters
